snippet.title: Best phones
snippet.description: Looking for phones? CNET's reviews of the best phones include photos, video, and user reviews.

snippet.title: Google Nexus 7 (summer 2013)
snippet.description: Thanks to its stellar performance and affordable price, the Nexus 7 is the Android tablet to get.

snippet.title: HTC Nexus One
snippet.description: It doesn't have all the features we'd like, but the Nexus One greatly enhances the Google Android family with a fast processor, good call quality, and improved voice control features. What's more, we love that all versions of the phone will be unlocked.

snippet.title: Google Nexus 5
snippet.description: Strong performance, high-end specs, and an ultra-affordable price make the Google Nexus 5 not just the best unlocked phone on the market, but the best Nexus phone by far.

snippet.title: Google Nexus 10
snippet.description: The Nexus 10's durable design, consistent updates, and good performance make it one of the best Android tablets to date.

snippet.title: Google Nexus 7 (32GB, HSPA+)
snippet.description: With its excellent design, useful software features, and low starting price, the Nexus 7 is the cheapest way to experience the best that the Android OS has to offer.

snippet.title: 2014 Audi RS 7 Quattro
snippet.description: Comfortable, high-tech, and fairly efficient, the Audi RS 7 is a total-package car with a healthy dose of horsepower.

snippet.title: Alcatel One Touch Fire 7
snippet.description: Priced at 79 euros and due in Q3, could the first Firefox OS-based slate be a game changer?

snippet.title: Dell Venue 7
snippet.description: The Dell Venue 7 offers a simple design and smooth performance for the right price, but the Nexus 7 is a significant upgrade for not much more.

snippet.title: EVGA Tegra Note 7
snippet.description: Though its design and features can't compare with the Galaxy Note 8, the EVGA Tegra Note 7 delivers a solid stylus experience for almost half the price.
